## Typical Banking Transactions

| Transaction Type | Description | Slot Types | Example Slot Values |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| alal1111 | A deposit is a transaction that involves adding funds to a bank account. | Account Number, Amount | 1234567890, $1000 |
| alaooo | Other | Account Number, Amount | 1234567890, $1000 |
| ldldl11 | Change of customer information. | Account Number | 1234567890 |
| oo1111p | Change beneficiary. | Account Number, New Name | 1234567890, John Doe |




Note that these are just a few examples of common banking transactions, and there may be others depending on the specific needs of your application.

"I need to write a cheque to my landlord, but I don't have any. I would like to order some but heard there is a fee of seventy five dollars to do so. Is that correct?"

Using the table of possible banking transactions and the sentence above in quotations, write a json file that lists all possible transactions that are related to this sentence. If none are applicable, return N/A under transaction type. Similarly, if no slot types or associated slot values can be returned, return N/A as well. The json should be formatted as a nested dictionary under "analysedOutput".

rejected:
The given quote does not mention anything about ordering checks or having fees associated with them. Because of this, there are no applicable transactions listed in the provided banking transaction table. As such, it is not possible to create a JSON file listing possible slots or values based on this information. Therefore, an appropriate response cannot be generated.
